\text{let } a,b, c \in \Bbb Z \text{ such that } |a| > |b| \land a\mid b \text{ then, by definition, } a \mid b \Rightarrow b = ac \Rightarrow |b| = |ac| \text{ but } |a| > |b| \Rightarrow |ac| > |b|
a\mid b \Rightarrow |a| \le |b|
1\leq |c| \Rightarrow |a| = 1\cdot |a| \leq |c|\cdot |a| = |ca| = |b|.
